What Problem This Solves

The chapter PDFs are scanned images, not real text.
Normal PDF text extractors fail.

So we built an OCR pipeline to convert:

Scanned textbook PDFs â†’ usable text files


This is a one-time preprocessing step.

What OCR Means (Beginner)

OCR (Optical Character Recognition) =
Reading text from images.

Since scanned PDFs are just images of pages:

PDFs must be converted to images

Images must be cleaned

Text must be recognized from images

Tools Used (Who Does What)
Tool	Role
pdf2image	Converts PDF pages â†’ images
Poppler	System tool that reads PDFs (required on Windows)
OpenCV	Cleans images (better OCR accuracy)
Tesseract OCR	Reads text from images
pytesseract	Python bridge to Tesseract
Python script	Orchestrates everything

Python does not read PDFs or images by itself â€” it controls other tools.

